'''Shiogama Shrine''' (鹽竈神社, Shiogama Jinja) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:港区|Minato, Tokyo]], [[:en:Tokyo|Tokyo]].
== Overview == In [[:en:1695|1695]] ([[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 8), [[:en:Date Tsunamura|Date Tsunamura]], the {{ill|daimyō|ja|藩主|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/daimyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 藩}} of [[:en:Sendai Domain|Sendai Domain]], enshrined a [[:en:Bunrei|divided spirit]] from the [[:en:Shiogama shrine|Shiogama Shrine]] in his domain and established the shrine within the {{ill|Edo upper residence|ja|江戸上屋敷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Edo upper residence|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 江戸藩邸}} of the Sendai Domain in [[:en:Shiodome|Shiodome]]<ref name="Historical Walk">Motoaki Tawara, "Minato-ku Historical Walk (Tokyo Historical Guide 3)," Gakuseisha, 1992, pp. 29-30</ref>.
In [[:en:1856|1856]] ([[:en:Ansei|Ansei]] 3), the shrine was relocated to the {{ill|Sendai Domain Edo Middle Residence|ja|仙台藩江戸中屋敷|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sendai Domain Edo Middle Residence|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, its current location, and opened for public worship. Even after the departure of the Sendai Domain officials in the [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji period]], the shrine continued to be revered as a deity of safe childbirth<ref name="Historical Walk"></ref>.
The shrine grounds were formerly part of the Sendai Domain's Edo residence and were owned by the Date family. In [[:en:1930|1930]] ([[:en:Shōwa era|Shōwa]] 5), in response to local requests, the then-head of the Date family, {{ill|Date Okimune|ja|伊達興宗|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Date Okimune|qq=}}, donated the land to the local [[:en:Chōnaikai|neighborhood association]], "Atago-shita Neighborhood Association." The area was subsequently opened as "Shiogama Park," Tokyo’s only park managed by a neighborhood association. In [[:en:1972|1972]] (Shōwa 47), the park was transferred to the administration of Minato Ward<ref name="Minato-ku">[https://www.city.minato.tokyo.jp/shisetsu/koen/shiba/06.html Shiogama Park] Minato-ku Shiba Area Comprehensive Office, Urban Development Division</ref>.
== Access == * A 5-minute walk from [[:en:Onarimon Station|Onarimon Station]] ({{OSM route map|start=35.66125,139.75173|goal=35.66321,139.75433|name=Route Guide}}).
